# Planner Orchestration

The user-started primary Cursor session is the planner. It may clarify intent,
inspect the repository, write or update specs/plans/ADRs, decompose work, assign
bounded work packets to custom agents, review their reports, and report status.

The primary must delegate all production/test edits, debugging, QA, review,
verification, Git operations, and PR operations. It must not execute those
steps itself or fall back to direct work when a worker is unavailable. Stop and
report the blocked phase instead.

Use Cursor's native custom-subagent invocation with roles from
`.cursor/agents/`. Never use Kandev MCP task/session APIs to launch or control
workers. Those APIs are only for explicit user requests to manage Kandev
platform tasks or sessions.

Each worker receives one bounded packet with owned files, acceptance criteria,
constraints, and a verification command. Workers execute only that packet and
must not spawn other agents. Follow-up fixes are new planner assignments.

When this session was invoked as a named role from `.cursor/agents/`, it is a
worker rather than the primary planner: execute the assigned packet, return a
compact result, and do not delegate.
